== About ==
==== A samll, interactive ruby command line client for xmms2 ====

the client itself is an irb shell executing commands on the client object, which has been extended to get a powerfull and easy interface to playback, playlists and collections. As it is all ruby, you can easily extend its functionality, create new aliases or functions, or create you own client ontop of it.

== Features ==
====Features for non-rubyists, the basics====
* usable without knowing ruby
* works an almost all terminal
* nice commandline interface with completion
* module support for new features
* allready has cool module: vote, mlib, ...
* short tutorial to get into the feeling of the client
* help system, so you don't get lost ;)

====Features for rubyists, advanced things====

* cool stack feature
* highly configurable and extensable
* esay to modify for your own needs
* you can do cool things, as all is ruby
   # remove unwanted media
   (url =~ 'file:///some/stage/music%').list.each{|id| medialib_entry_remove(id)}
   # wake me up with cool fadein
   sleep 60*60*8; (0...100).each{|i| volume i; sleep 0.1}
   # the stack feature
   stack.inject{|a,b| a|b}
   # tag media
   (url =~ 'anArtist/%').list.each do |s|
     if s.url =~ /\/(\w| )*\/(\w*) - (\w*)/
